# Presentation Branding Guidelines

This rule defines the standard branding elements to maintain a consistent visual identity throughout the presentation.

## Color Palette
- Primary: `#3980FB` (Main brand blue)
- Secondary: `#30D158` (Success/highlight green)
- Accent: `#FF9D0A` (Warning/attention orange)
- Background: `#1C1C1E` (Dark mode background)
- Text: `#FFFFFF` (Light text for dark backgrounds)

## Typography
- Headings: 'Source Sans Pro', sans-serif
- Body text: 'Open Sans', sans-serif
- Code: 'Fira Code', monospace
- Keep font sizes consistent:
  - h1: 3.5em
  - h2: 2.5em
  - h3: 1.8em
  - Body text: 1.5em
  - Code: 1.2em

## Logo Usage
- Place the Cursor logo in the bottom right corner of title slides
- Keep logo size consistent (recommend 150px width)
- Maintain clear space around the logo (at least 20px on all sides)
- Example logo placement:
```html
<section>
  <h1>Slide Title</h1>
  <img class="logo" src="assets/cursor-logo.png" alt="Cursor Logo" style="position: absolute; bottom: 20px; right: 20px; width: 150px;">
</section>
```

## Image Style
- Use consistent image style throughout:
  - Screenshots should have rounded corners (8px radius)
  - Apply subtle drop shadow to images: `box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2)`
  - Maintain aspect ratios, don't stretch or distort
- Example CSS:
```css
.reveal img:not(.logo) {
  border-radius: 8px;
  box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.2);
}
```

## Code Highlighting
- Use the "Atom One Dark" theme for code blocks
- Highlight important code sections with a yellow background:
```html
<pre><code data-line-numbers="3-5">...</code></pre>
```
- Keep syntax highlighting consistent (JavaScript, HTML, CSS, etc.)

## Slide Backgrounds
- Main title slides: Gradient background `linear-gradient(135deg, #3980FB 0%, #1E3C72 100%)`
- Regular content slides: Solid dark background `#1C1C1E`
- Special section dividers: Full-bleed relevant images with 40% dark overlay

Apply these branding guidelines consistently to maintain a professional and cohesive presentation style.
